dozers.insight: Less competition on weekends, cheaper CPCs

excavator.insight: Competitors bidding less aggressively on weekends

key_findings: Sunday had ZERO conversions across both campaigns - $232.32 wasted
Saturday CPA was 32-65% better than weekday average
Saturday ROAS was significantly worse (7.27x vs 18.94x for Dozers)
The 1 deal that closed on Saturday was later cancelled
~85% of Saturday leads wanted different equipment than searched (mini ex, skid steer)
Weekend searchers are small businesses/individuals wanting same-day rentals
Cannot fulfill same-day weekend orders due to supply sourcing
rationale: High equipment mismatch rate - wrong customer profile
Low CPA is misleading - leads don't convert to revenue
Cheap acquisition doesn't matter if customers have poor first experience
alternative_strategies: Use weekend landing page with Monday callback option
Focus budget on weekdays where fulfillment is possible
